@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}
<h2>@ViewBag.Title.</h2>
<h3>@ViewBag.Message</h3>

<p>
    The easiest way to view real-time log messages from distributed applications.
</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        Add the following appender to your logging configuration:<br />
        <pre>
&lt;appender name=&quot;UdpAppender&quot; type=&quot;log4net.Appender.UdpAppender&quot;&gt;
    &lt;param name=&quot;RemoteAddress&quot; value=&quot;@ViewBag.IpAddress&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;param name=&quot;RemotePort&quot; value=&quot;8080&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;layout type=&quot;log4net.Layout.XmlLayoutSchemaLog4j, log4net&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/appender&gt;</pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        In your code, create a unique ID for your application. Any string will work. GUIDs are fine. Here is one for free!<br />
        <pre>log4net.GlobalContext.Properties["ApplicationId"] = "@ViewBag.NewGuid";</pre>
    </li>
    <li>View your log messages in real time on the @Html.ActionLink("home page!", "Index", "Home")</li>
</ol>
